<p style="color: green"><%= notice %></p>

<% content_for :title, "Question Details" %>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 mt-16">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <nav class="text-sm mb-6 text-base-content/70">
      <%= link_to "Questions", questions_path, class: "hover:text-accent" %> /
      <span class="text-base-content">Question Details</span>
    </nav>

    <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
      <!-- Sample Question Content - In a real app, this would be dynamic with @question data -->
      <div class="p-6">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
          <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-base-content">How to help my child explore gender identity?</h1>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-warning/20 text-warning rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Pending</span>
        </div>

        <div class="prose max-w-none text-base-content/90 mb-4">
          <p>My 11-year-old has recently started questioning their gender identity. They've mentioned feeling uncomfortable with some gendered expectations and have asked about trying different pronouns.</p>
          <p>I want to be supportive but I'm not sure how to navigate this conversation. What resources are available for parents in my situation? Are there age-appropriate books or other materials I could share with them? How can I create a supportive environment while also being mindful that they're still exploring?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center mt-8 pb-4 border-b border-base-300">
          <div class="avatar">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center text-primary font-bold">
              JD
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ml-3">
            <p class="font-medium">Jane D.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/60">September 2, 2023 • 10:14 AM</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Response Section - Would only display for appropriate roles or once answered -->
        <div class="mt-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Status Updates</h2>

          <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="avatar">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent flex items-center justify-center text-accent-content font-bold">
                  DR
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="ml-3">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-base-content">Dr. Robin Taylor</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">Gender Studies Professor • September 3, 2023</p>
                <p class="mt-2 text-base-content/90">I'll be providing an answer to this question shortly. I'm gathering some resources that would be helpful for this situation.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- For admin/responder view -->
          <div class="mt-6 p-4 border border-base-300 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-medium text-base-content mb-2">Add a Response</h3>
            <textarea class="w-full border border-base-300 rounded-md p-3 min-h-[120px] bg-base-100" placeholder="Type your response here..."></textarea>
            <div class="flex justify-end mt-3 gap-2">
              <button class="btn btn-sm">Save Draft</button>
              <button class="btn btn-sm btn-accent">Publish Response</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 flex justify-between">
      <%= link_to "← Back to questions", questions_path, class: "text-accent hover:underline" %>

      <div class="space-x-2">
        <%= link_to "Edit", edit_question_path(@question), class: "btn btn-sm" %>
        <%= button_to "Delete", @question, method: :delete, class: "btn btn-sm btn-error", form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "Are you sure you want to delete this question?" } } %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
